{"title":"Elite Rizer simulates climbing, descending, AND steering for realistic trainer workouts","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/26/elite-rizer-simulates-climbing-descending-and-steering-for-realistic-trainer-workouts/","date":1627316497000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>We’re still a ways off from a completely immersive cycling simulator, but thanks to products like the new Elite Rizer — we’re getting closer. Riders looking for the most realistic training while stationary indoors now have a new option for the front end. The Elite Rizer combines a motorized fork support that also allows for steering input to take your Zwifting to the next level.</p><h2>Gradient Simulator</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x424/rscb26/ng:webp/ngcb26\" alt=\"Elite Rizer gradient simulator\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1051\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-297x260.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-800x701.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-120x105.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-768x673.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-696x610.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-1068x935.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-480x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 480w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x424/rscb26/ng:webp/ngcb26\" ezoid=\"0.9052400936105567\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-297x260.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-800x701.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-120x105.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-768x673.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-696x610.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-1068x935.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113911/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-2-480x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb26 480w\"></a></p><p>Just what is a ‘gradient simulator?’ Well, it starts with removing the front wheel of your bike. You then attach your fork dropouts to the ‘hub’ on the Rizer, and it uses motors to raise or lower the front end of the bike. This simulates the positioning you’d get while riding, which in turn helps use different muscle groups than you would use just training in one position.</p><p>The Rizer provides up to +20% inclines, and -10% declines, which puts it on par with the Wahoo KICKR CLIMB. Thanks to built in Bluetooth and ANT+, the Rizer will communicate directly with programs like Zwift to emulate the grades in the game, automatically rising or lowering based on the virtual terrain.</p><p>If you’d rather control things manually, there are controls on the top of the unit to allow you to do just that. It’s also controllable through the Rizer app for iOS and Android devices.</p><figure id=\"attachment_266464\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-266464\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113928/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-9.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.co