accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-9.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113928/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-9-297x277.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113928/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-9-800x747.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113928/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-9-120x112.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113928/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-9-768x717.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113928/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-9-696x650.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113928/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-9-1068x997.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113928/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-9-450x420.jpg 450w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-266464\">&nbsp;</figcaption></figure><p>However, the Rizer sets itself apart by incorporating steering functionality into the fork mount. It appears that this allow the fork to rotate, and also move side to side for realistic movement. What’s not known is the range of steering — we’ve found some of these steering devices to be limiting on games like Hustle City where gameplay requires big corrections, but the turning radius of the steering device prevents you from doing so.</p><p>Like the incline/decline, steering is enabled with Bluetooth and ANT+ meaning you won’t need to use your phone as a steering sensor for various games or training programs.</p><h2>Elite Rizer Details &amp; Pricing</h2><figure id=\"attachment_266462\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-266462\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4.jpg\" alt=\"Automatic fork raiser for indoor cycling+\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1601\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-225x300.jpg 225w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-800x1067.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-90x120.jpg 90w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-768x1025.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-1151x1536.jpg 1151w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-696x929.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-1068x1425.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-315x420.jpg 315w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-225x300.jpg 225w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-800x1067.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-90x120.jpg 90w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-768x1025.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-1151x1536.jpg 1151w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-696x929.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-1068x1425.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/26113916/Elite-Rizer-trainer-accessory-riser-fork-block-steering-4-315x420.jpg 315w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-266462\">&nbsp;</figcaption></figure><p>Elite also claims that the Rizer is the most stable device of its kind thanks to a rigid aluminum and steel structure with four adjustable feet. Still, there is a weight limit of 264.5lbs, which we’d assume includes the weight of your bike (sans front wheel).</p><p>Compatible with most bikes, the Rizer includes fitments for QR, 12×100, 15×100, and 15×110 thru axles. Basically everything except bikes with 20mm axles, or fat bikes.</p><p>Elite says the Rizer is compatible with the Direto XR, Direto XR-T, Suito, Suito-T, and Tuo trainers, but there’s no reason to believe it shouldn’t be compatible with trainers from other brands as well. Elite also states that the Rizer is compatible with Zwift, The SufferFest, Ful Gaz, RGT, Bkool, and more training apps.</p><p>Priced at $1,099.99, expect the Rizer to be available in the U.S. this fall.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.elite-it.com/en/products/home-trainers/ecosystem-accessories/rizer?utm_source=newsletter_en&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=RIZER_2021#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>elite-it.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"ce703900cbfb21f25f686b7823d290506e899954915835807ff4bde0af300487","category":"Cycling"}